memberdef.argsstring: (final Configuration a_conf, int a_lowerBounds, int a_upperBounds)
memberdef.name: NumberGeneImpl

detaileddescription.para: Retrieves a string representation of the value of this Gene instance that includes any information required to reconstruct it at a later time, such as its value and internal state. This string will be used to represent this Gene instance in XML persistence. This is an optional method but, if not implemented, XML persistence and possibly other features will not be available. An UnsupportedOperationException should be thrown if no implementation is provided.

simplesect.para: string representation of this Gene's current state

parameterdescription.para: to indicate that no implementation is provided for this method

detaileddescription.para: Sets the value and internal state of this Gene from the string representation returned by a previous invocation of the getPersistentRepresentation() method. This is an optional method but, if not implemented, XML persistence and possibly other features will not be available. An UnsupportedOperationException should be thrown if no implementation is provided.

parameterdescription.para: the string representation retrieved from a prior call to the getPersistentRepresentation() method
to indicate that no implementation is provided for this method
if this Gene implementation does not support the given string representation

detaileddescription.para: Sets the value of this Gene to a random legal value for the implementation. This method exists for the benefit of mutation and other operations that simply desire to randomize the value of a gene.

parameterdescription.para: The random number generator that should be used to create any random values. It's important to use this generator to maintain the user's flexibility to configure the genetic engine to use the random number generator of their choice

detaileddescription.para:
Applies a mutation of a given intensity (percentage) onto the atomic element at given index (NumberGenes only have one atomic element)
index
index of atomic element, between 0 and size()-1
a_percentage
percentage of mutation (greater than -1 and smaller than 1).
1.1

Maps the value of this NumberGene to within the bounds specified by the m_upperBounds and m_lowerBounds instance variables. The value's relative position within the integer range will be preserved within the bounds range (in other words, if the value is about halfway between the integer max and min, then the resulting value will be about halfway between the upper bounds and lower bounds). If the value is null or is already within the bounds, it will be left unchanged.
Compares to objects by first casting them into their expected type (e.g. Integer for IntegerGene) and then calling the compareTo-method of the casted type.

parameterdescription.para: first object to be compared, always is not null
second object to be compared, always is not null

simplesect.para: a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this object is less than, equal to, or greater than the object provided for comparison

detaileddescription.para: Test implementation of NumberGene, based on IntegerGene.
